OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1783950571
OL,3,CGreenisland houses destroyed by fire
OL,4,Cprompt investigation
OL,6,FAn investigation is under way into the
OL,7,Fcause of a fire which destroyed two
OL,8,Fhouses in Co Antrim.
OL,10,FThe incident in Greenisland, near
OL,11,FCarrickfergus, also saw two other
OL,12,Fterraced properties damaged in the
OL,13,Fearly hours of Sunday morning.
OL,15,FNorthern Ireland Fire and Rescue
OL,16,FService (NIFRS) Area Commander Dermot
OL,17,FRooney said: "In Greenisland,
OL,18,FCarrickfergus, firefighters dealt with
OL,19,Fa row of terraced houses on fire,
OL,20,Falong with two oil tanks and a shed.
OL,26,@yD@NOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/5
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,416,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1783950571
OL,3,CGreenisland houses destroyed by fire
OL,4,Cprompt investigation
OL,6,F"Two homes were completely destroyed
OL,7,Fwith damage caused to a further two
OL,8,Fproperties.
OL,10,F"The cause of the fire is under
OL,11,Finvestigation."
OL,13,FA PSNI spokesperson said: "Police
OL,14,Fprovided assistance to colleagues at
OL,15,Fthe Northern Ireland Fire and Rescue
OL,16,FService following a report of fire
OL,17,Fdamage caused to properties in the
OL,18,FKnockleigh Walk area of Greenisland.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUsD@OO]uD@[OU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/5
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,416,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1783950571
OL,3,CGreenisland houses destroyed by fire
OL,4,Cprompt investigation
OL,6,F"The report for assistance was made to
OL,7,Fpolice at approximately 12.20am this
OL,8,Fmorning, Sunday 12th July."
OL,10,FThe PSNI said the fire "has been
OL,11,Fdeemed accidental at this time".
OL,13,FAlliance Party councillor Stewart
OL,14,FDickson, who lives in the area,
OL,15,Fexpressed his sympathies to the
OL,16,Ffamilies impacted by the fire.
OL,18,FHe said: "I'd like to express my
OL,19,Fthanks to the wonderful neighbours who
OL,20,Fopened their homes to the families
OL,21,Fwhose homes were destroyed last night.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@[O]rD@XOUsD@_O]zD@JOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/5
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,416,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1783950571
OL,3,CGreenisland houses destroyed by fire
OL,4,Cprompt investigation
OL,6,F"The whole Greenisland community
OL,7,Freally rallied around the victims of
OL,8,Fthe fire.
OL,10,F"I'd also like to thank the Northern
OL,11,FIreland Fire & Rescue Service and all
OL,12,Fother agencies involved in getting the
OL,13,Fsituation under control.
OL,15,F"Thankfully, no one was hurt or
OL,16,Finjured; however, this has been an
OL,17,Fextremely distressing situation for
OL,18,Fthe entire community in Greenisland,
OL,19,Fin which I live, and what we need now
OL,20,Fis a full and thorough investigation
OL,21,Finto exactly what caused this fire."
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUwD@AOU}D@dO]
